html

css

background-size: cover; fills the entire width, cropping/zooming to maintain aspect ratio.

3 Ways to Fix the Zoom Issue

Below are the best adjustments you can make.

OPTION 1 Use background-size: contain (No Zoom, Full Fit)

This prevents cropping and zooming:

css
.s-banner .swiper-slide {
    background-size: contain !important;
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    background-position: center;
    background-color: #000; /* optional */
}

Image shows fully
Might leave empty space top/bottom depending on screen
Best if you want exact image visible with no cropping.

OPTION 2 Adjust Position to Reveal More of the Image

If you just want the image to zoom less or show more content:

css
.s-banner .swiper-slide {
    background-size: cover;
    background-position: top center; /* or 'bottom center' */
}

Try these variants:

  • center top = shows upper part

  • center bottom = shows lower part (hard hat & plans)

Best if the bottom part of the image is what you want visible.

OPTION 3 Reduce Zoom by Changing background-size

css
.s-banner .swiper-slide {

}

Example values to test:

  • 100%

  • 110%

  • 120%

Best if you want it to fill nicely but not be overly cropped.

    height: auto;
}

/* Force service-body (text section) to stretch */
.services-body {
    flex: 1;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
}

/* Push the button to the bottom */
.services-btn {
    margin-top: auto; 
}

WHY THE PREVIOUS FIX DID NOT WORK

Your original structure is likely:

css
.services-row (NOT flex container)
    .services-item
        .services-thumb
        .services-body

Since .services-row was not a flexbox,
.services-item could NOT stretch to equal heights.

By converting .services-row into display:flex, all cards now match height.
